test_ProjectCodeCombine module¶

File Description:¶

This file contains tests for all functions we used. For example, we ensure the column names are correct in the dataset fed into the visualization function draw_FIrate(), it must be pd.DataFrame with a shape of (28282, 3), and columns ‘FIPS’, ‘Rate of Food Insecurity’, ‘year’. In addition to this test, we also ensure the output types and information of other functions.

test_ProjectCodeCombine.test_draw_FIrate()¶

This function test if vdraw_FIrate works well. It ensures it outputs a pd.DataFrame, and the dataframe has shape (28282,3), and columns as shown below.

test_ProjectCodeCombine.test_prepare_data()¶

This function test if prepare data function works well. It ensures prepare_data()

Return

returns a pd.DataFrame that has shape (58,7), and has column names as shown as below.

test_ProjectCodeCombine.test_rank_county()¶

This function test if rank_county function works well. It test if its output is a pd.DataFrame with shape (58, 13), and the columns of the dataframe is as shown below.

test_ProjectCodeCombine.test_result_visual()¶

This funtion test if result_visual works well. It first prepare data, and use the data for rank_county. Then its output is fed in to result_visual, and check if the output is go.Figure.
